examples.en: She's busy preparing for her test.
He's preparing for his move to California.
When we got home, Stephano was busy preparing dinner.
Her parents were busy preparing to go on holiday.
The company is preparing for zero growth (=no growth) this year.
He is preparing a run for the presidency.
A photographer is preparing to take a view of the castle.
The opposing armies were preparing for war.
They are preparing to pull back their forces.
Farmers are busy preparing the soil for planting.
I'm preparing a speech for the meeting on Thursday.
She whispered to us that she was preparing a party.
The sailors are preparing themselves for a long voyage.
Sara had the task of preparing the agenda for meetings.
The army is preparing to make a stand against the enemy.
The team is preparing for another tilt at the European Cup.
Now he is occupied with data treatment, preparing articles.
The dentist took an impression for use in preparing an inlay.
The discussions were preliminary to preparing a policy paper.
The mayor urged citizens to begin preparing for a major storm.
They were preparing children to sit for the entry examination.
Health education will play a part in preparing us for old age.
The ageing president is preparing to transfer power to his son.
The Chicago Bears are busy preparing themselves for the big game.
Coulthard's team were up all night preparing the car for the race.
Green set himself the task of preparing a map of this remote area.
Having clean hands is one of the cardinal rules when preparing food.
Outside there are a lot of "cabooses" for preparing fish in the open air.
The nation's pediatrician laureate is preparing to lay down his black bag.
I'm preparing the results of my study for submission to a medical journal.
